[{"id":"VR794766","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<div>Assuming gravitational forces are negligible, which of the following best indicates the magnitude and direction of the force exerted on the particle as it enters the magnetic field?</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n","rubricRef":"VR794766_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">A particle with charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative 2 e\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"negative 2 e\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>e</mi></math></span></span> travels to the right with a speed of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3.0 times 10 cubed, meters per second\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"3.0 times 10 cubed, meters per second\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mn>3.0</mn> <mo>×</mo> <msup> <mn>10</mn> <mn>3</mn> </msup> <mspace width=\"0.2em\"> </mspace> <mtext>m</mtext> <mo>/</mo> <mtext>s</mtext> </math></span></span> when it enters a region with a uniform magnetic field of magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.5 teslas\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1.5 teslas\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1.5</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>T</mtext></math></span></span> directed towards the bottom of the page, as shown.</div>\n\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a particle moving to the right toward a region with a uniform magnetic field of magnitude 1.5 teslas directed downward. The particle has charge negative 2 e and is moving to the right with speed 3 times 10 cubed, meters per second.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR794766.g01.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><